After deposing their father Cronus, Poseidon, Zeus, and Hades shot dice in a helmet for lordship of the world. Zeus won the sky, Hades the underworld, and Poseidon the sea.<br>
The rather surly and quarrelsome Poseidon is equal to his brother Zeus in dignity, but not in power. He built an underwater palace and large stables where he kept white chariot horses with golden manes and brazen hooves. Whenever the horses drew Poseidon in a golden chariot, storms ceased and dolphins rose playfully around the chariot.<br>
