Needing a wife who would be at home in the sea, he approached Amphirite the Nereid. She found Poseidon repugnant and fled, but he sent one Delphinus to plead his case. Delphinus did so well pleading, that Amphirite yielded and consented to the marriage. Gratefully, Poseidon set Delphinus's image among the stars as the constellation, the Dolphin.<br>
<br>
Amphirite bore him three children. She was jealous of his various love affairs, once changing a rival into a barking monster with six heads and twelve feet.<br>
